30/06/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Appeals Court in Belgrade reduced the sentences Tuesday (June 29th) of four radical Islamists convicted of terrorism and assassination plots in 2009. 
Adnan Hot's sentence was reduced from eight to 7.5 years; Fuad Hodzic's -- from 7.5 to seven, while the sentences of Mirsad Prentic and Erhan Smailovic went from seven to 6.5 years. 
The four were part of a group of 12 Serb Muslims, believed to be followers of the Wahhabi movement. 
Most of them were arrested in 2007 near Novi Pazar. 
(Beta, AFP, RTS - 29/06/10)
